'''Aditya Pancholi''' (born '''Nirmal Pancholi''') is an Indian [[film actor]], [[Film producer|producer]] and [[playback singer]] who appears in [[Bollywood]] films. He started his career as a lead actor, though he was more successful in supporting roles and as an antagonist. He received a [[Filmfare]] nomination for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Performance in a Negative Role|Best Performance in a Negative Role]] for ''[[Yes Boss (film)|Yes Boss]]'' (1997).

Pancholi began his career with television movies produced by Nari Hira and ventured into mainstream Bollywood cinema with ''Sasti Dulhan Mehnga Dulha'' (1986). Pancholi first came into the limelight with an important role in ''[[Maha-Sangram]]'' (1990). He had the peak of his career between the late 1980s and early 1990s. He succeeded by playing the second lead; most of his leading roles were not box office successes.

==ᱟᱬᱜᱟᱛ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ᱟᱨ ᱜᱷᱟᱨᱚᱸᱡᱽ==
Aditya Pancholi is the son of the filmmaker Rajan Pancholi and Aruna Pancholi.He belongs to the [[Pancholi]] community. He has one sister and two brothers. He received his early education from [[St. Joseph's High School, Juhu|St. Joseph's High School]] in Juhu, Mumbai. In 1986, Pancholi married actress [[Zarina Wahab]] and they have two children, Sooraj (b. 9 November 1990) and Sana Pancholi.

Sooraj made his acting debut in ''[[Hero (2015 Hindi film)|Hero]]'' (2015).

